\f0\fs24 \cf0 Dialogue Summarization Project\
\
 Problem Statement and Business Context\
This project focuses on summarizing dialogues into concise and meaningful summaries. Dialogue summarization is a critical task in natural language processing (NLP) with applications in customer support, meeting transcription, and chatbot development. The SAMSum dataset, which contains human-annotated summaries of dialogues, is used for training and evaluation.\
\
 Technical Approach \
1. Dataset:\
   - The SAMSum dataset is used, containing dialogues and their corresponding summaries.\
   - A subset of the dataset (20%) is used to reduce computational cost.\
\
2. Model:\
   - An encoder-decoder architecture is implemented using pre-trained BERT models:\
     - Encoder: `distilbert-base-uncased`\
     - Decoder: `prajjwal1/bert-small`\
   - Cross-attention is enabled in the decoder to improve the quality of generated summaries.\
\
3. Training:\
   - The model is trained using the PyTorch framework.\
   - Gradient accumulation is used to simulate a larger batch size.\
   - The loss function is Cross-Entropy Loss.\
\
4.Evaluation:\
   - ROUGE scores (ROUGE-1, ROUGE-2, ROUGE-L) are used to evaluate the quality of generated summaries.\
\
5. Visualization:\
   - Training loss and ROUGE scores are plotted to monitor model performance.\
\
Results and Evaluation\
- Training Loss: Decreases over epochs, indicating successful learning.\
- **ROUGE Scores**:\
  - ROUGE-1: 0.205\
  - ROUGE-2: 0.033\
  - ROUGE-L: 0.13\
\
The model demonstrates the ability to generate meaningful summaries, though there is room for improvement.\
\
 Discussion of Limitations and Future Work\
 Limitations:\
- Small Dataset: Only 20% of the SAMSum dataset is used, which limits the model's learning capacity.\
- Model Size**: Smaller models are used due to computational constraints, which may impact performance.\
\
Future Work:\
- Use larger pre-trained models (e.g., BERT-large, T5).\
- Train on the full SAMSum dataset or other dialogue datasets.\
- Experiment with advanced techniques like reinforcement learning for sequence generation.\
\
